---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="FAQ - BL4Codes">
	<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
		<!-- Page title -->
		<div class="text-center mb-12">
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-4">‚ùì Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
			<p class="text-xl text-gray-300">Answers to your common questions about Borderlands 4 Shift Codes</p>
		</div>

		<!-- FAQ content -->
		<div class="space-y-8">
			<!-- Basic questions -->
			<section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center">
					üîß <span class="ml-2">Basic Questions</span>
				</h2>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What are SHiFT Codes?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">SHiFT Codes are special codes provided by Gearbox Software that players can redeem in-game to receive various rewards such as Golden Keys, Diamond Keys, weapons, Eridium, and equipment.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Are the codes free?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">Yes! All SHiFT Codes are provided by the official sources for free. Our website collects and organizes these free codes to make it easier for players to get the latest information.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What are the sources of codes?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">Our codes mainly come from:</p>
						<ul class="mt-2 ml-4 list-disc text-gray-300">
							<li>Gearbox Software official social media</li>
							<li>Borderlands official website</li>
							<li>Reddit community sharing</li>
							<li>Official events and live streams</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Usage questions -->
			<section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center">
					üéÆ <span class="ml-2">Usage Questions</span>
				</h2>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<div class="border-l-4 border-orange-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What to do if a code doesn't work?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300 mb-2">If a code doesn't work, please check the following:</p>
						<ul class="ml-4 list-disc text-gray-300 space-y-1">
							<li>Confirm if the code has expired</li>
							<li>Check if the code is compatible with your gaming platform</li>
							<li>Ensure the code format is correct (25 characters with hyphens)</li>
							<li>Verify you haven't already used this code</li>
							<li>Check if game servers are working properly</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Why do some codes show "expired"?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">Many codes have time limits, usually expiring within days to weeks after being published. We update code status in real-time, and expired codes will be marked as "expired".</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-yellow-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Where can I view rewards?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">After successfully redeeming a code, rewards will be sent to the in-game mailbox system. Find the "Mail" option in the main menu or pause menu to view and collect rewards.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Can I use the same code multiple times?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">No. Each SHiFT Code can only be used once per account. If you try to use an already redeemed code, the system will show "code already used".</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Platform questions -->
			<section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center">
					üñ•Ô∏è <span class="ml-2">Platform Questions</span>
				</h2>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<div class="border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Do all codes support all platforms?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">No. Codes are divided into:</p>
						<ul class="mt-2 ml-4 list-disc text-gray-300">
							<li><strong>Universal codes</strong>: Support PC, PlayStation, Xbox all platforms</li>
							<li><strong>Platform-specific codes</strong>: Only support specific platforms</li>
						</ul>
						<p class="text-gray-300 mt-2">We clearly label the supported platforms for each code.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What does PC platform include?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">PC platform usually includes:</p>
						<ul class="mt-2 ml-4 list-disc text-gray-300">
							<li>Steam</li>
							<li>Epic Games Store</li>
							<li>Other PC gaming platforms</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Website questions -->
			<section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center">
					üåê <span class="ml-2">Website Questions</span>
				</h2>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">How often are codes updated?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">We get the latest codes in real-time through our automatic monitoring system, usually with daily updates. When official new codes are released, we sync them to the website within minutes.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">How to know when new codes are available?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">You can:</p>
						<ul class="mt-2 ml-4 list-disc text-gray-300">
							<li>Visit our website regularly to check for latest codes</li>
							<li>Bookmark the website for quick access</li>
							<li>Follow our information sources (such as official social media)</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-cyan-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Is the website safe?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">Yes, our website is safe:</p>
						<ul class="mt-2 ml-4 list-disc text-gray-300">
							<li>We don't collect user personal information</li>
							<li>All codes are publicly available for free</li>
							<li>The website uses HTTPS encrypted connection</li>
							<li>We don't require user registration or login</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Other questions -->
			<section class="bg-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
				<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6 flex items-center">
					üí° <span class="ml-2">Other Questions</span>
				</h2>
				<div class="space-y-6">
					<div class="border-l-4 border-amber-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Can I share codes with friends?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">Yes! Each code can be used by multiple different accounts (unless it's a limited quantity code). However, note that each account can only use each code once.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-teal-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">What to do if I find incorrect information?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">If you find incorrect code information or encounter website issues, please contact us at support@bl4codes.com and we'll resolve it as soon as possible.</p>
					</div>

					<div class="border-l-4 border-rose-500 pl-6">
						<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">Is the website officially affiliated?</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-300">We are an independent fan website with no official affiliation with Gearbox Software. We only collect and organize publicly available code information to provide convenient services for the gaming community.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>
		</div>

		<!-- Contact information -->
		<div class="mt-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-500/10 to-red-500/10 border border-orange-500/20 rounded-lg p-6 text-center">
			<h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Have other questions?</h3>
			<p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">If you couldn't find an answer to your question here, feel free to contact us</p>
			<a href="mailto:support@bl4codes.com" class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-orange-600 hover:bg-orange-700 text-white rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors">
				üìß Send Email
			</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

